
 
CS 255 Business Requirements Document 

System Components and Design
Purpose
•	DriverPass needs a system that supports online practice exams/classes and on-the-road driving lesson scheduling.
•	The goal of this project is to design a web-based, cloud-hosted system that:
o	Supports multiple roles (customers, secretary, IT officer, owner/management)
o	Allow students to schedule, change, and cancel lessons online.
o	Tracks progress on practice tests and lesson history
o	Offers reports that can be printed or exported in formats compatible with Excel.
o	Tracks user actions for accountability (audit history)
________________________________________
System Background
•	DriverPass observes that a considerable number of students do not pass the DMV test, often because they rely on outdated practice exams rather than mastering current regulations and practical driving abilities.
•	DriverPass’s solution is a combined service offering:
o	Online learning (classes and practice tests)
o	Behind-the-wheel training (two-hour driving sessions with trainers, using DriverPass vehicles)
•	The system must include components for:
o	User account management and role permissions
o	Package registration and management (Packages 1–3; ability to disable a package)
o	Reservation scheduling tied to drivers and vehicles.
o	Online test tracking and progress dashboards
o	Driver notes / lesson history
o	Reporting and exports
o	Audit logging and activity reporting.
o	DMV update notification process (so content stays current)
________________________________________
Objectives and Goals
•	The system shall allow customers to create and manage accounts, including password resets.
•	The system shall allow customers to schedule, cancel, and modify two-hour driving lessons online.
•	The system shall allow the secretary to schedule lessons for customers (phone/in-office).
•	The system shall record reservations with customer, date, start time, end time, assigned driver, and assigned car.
•	The system shall support three training packages and allow management to disable packages from first-time registration.
•	The system shall track practice tests with test name, time taken, score, and status (not taken, in progress, failed, passed).
•	The system should store and display driver notes and lesson history.
•	The system should provide printable/exportable reports, including activity reports.
•	The system shall maintain an audit trail of reservation changes and record updates.
•	The system must provide notifications whenever DMV rules or questions are updated to ensure training remains up to date.
________________________________________
Nonfunctional Requirements
Performance Requirements
•	The system should be web-based and accessible on both desktop and mobile browsers.
•	The system shall support multiple concurrent users (students, staff, admin).
•	The system shall load key pages (login, schedule, test dashboard) within reasonable response times under normal load.
•	The system should support routine updates to test content when DMV information changes.
•	The system shall generate reports and exports within a reasonable period.
________________________________________
Platform Constraints
•	The system should be hosted in a cloud environment to reduce DriverPass responsibility for backups and security.
•	The system should run on modern browsers (Chrome, Edge, Safari, Firefox).
•	The system shall support access from computers and mobile devices.
•	The system shall store data in a database (users/roles, packages, reservations, drivers/cars, tests/results, driver notes, audit logs).
•	The system shall support exporting reports into formats compatible with Excel.
________________________________________
Accuracy and Precision
•	The system shall uniquely identify each user with a unique account identifier.
•	The system shall validate user input for registration, scheduling, and updates.
•	The system shall enforce lesson duration as two-hour sessions and store accurate start/end times.
•	The system shall prevent double-booking of drivers and cars in the same time slot.
•	The system shall notify authorized users when conflicts or critical errors occur.
•	The system shall record audit logs accurately (user, action, timestamp, record affected).
________________________________________
Adaptability
•	The system shall allow the IT officer to reset passwords and disable accounts as needed.
•	The system shall allow management to disable a package so new customers cannot register for it.
•	The system should support updates to training content and practice tests when DMV information changes.
•	The system shall support future enhancements without requiring a full redesign of the system foundation.
________________________________________
Security
•	The system should require authentication for any account-specific functions.
•	The system shall enforce role-based access control:
o	Customer: schedule/cancel/modify their own reservations; take tests; view progress/results
o	Secretary: schedule/cancel/modify reservations for customers; view schedules
o	IT Officer: full administrative access for user management and access control
o	Owner/Management: access reports, schedules, and oversight data
•	The system should provide a secure password reset process for customers.
•	The system should protect sensitive customer and employee data using least privilege of access.
•	The system shall log key actions for accountability (reservation actions and record changes).
________________________________________
Functional Requirements
•	The system allows customers to register an account with personal and contact information.
•	The system shall allow customers to select a training package during registration.
•	The system shall allow management to disable packages so new customers cannot register for them.
•	The system allows customers to schedule two-hour driving lesson reservations online.
•	The system allows customers to cancel and modify their reservations online.
•	The system shall allow the secretary to schedule, cancel, and modify reservations on behalf of customers.
•	The system shall store reservation details including date, start time, end time, customer, assigned driver, and assigned car.
•	The system shall prevent double-booking of drivers or cars for the same date/time slot.
•	The system shall provide online practice tests and record results including score, time taken, and status.
•	The system shall display practice test progress and history for each customer.
•	The system shall store driver notes and lesson history tied to lessons.
•	The system shall generate reports for authorized users, including activity reports and scheduling reports.
•	The system shall log user activity for reservation creation, modification, and cancellation, including who performed each action and when.
•	The system should notify authorized staff when DMV updates occur so content can be reviewed and updated.
________________________________________
User Interface
•	The system should provide a web-based interface that is easy to use and mobile-friendly.
•	The system shall include pages for:
o	Login/logout
o	Registration and package selection
o	Password reset
o	Scheduling calendar and time selection
o	Reservation management (view, cancel, modify)
o	Practice test dashboard (test name, time taken, score, status)
o	Lesson history and driver notes display
o	Staff scheduling tools for secretary/admin roles.
o	Reporting page (print/export)
o	Contact page for contacting DriverPass and contacting customers.
________________________________________
Assumptions
•	Users must be online to schedule, modify, or cancel reservations and to take practice tests.
•	DriverPass will keep driver and vehicle availability information current in the system.
•	DMV updates will be available through a process DriverPass can access (manual or integrated).
•	Payment processing should be managed through a secure payment processor rather than storing raw credit card data directly in the system.
________________________________________
Limitations
•	Offline scheduling/editing is not supported due to the risk of conflicting or duplicating records.
•	Full package customization (adding/removing package modules without developer involvement) is out of scope for the current release; disabling a package is sufficient.
•	The DMV update method depends on DMV capabilities and DriverPass access.
•	Time, staffing, and budget constraints may limit features beyond the core scheduling/testing/tracking requirements.
